data.text: build ♦ construct ♦ assemble ♦ erect ♦ set up ♦ put up ♦ put together

data.chText: 以上各词均含制造、建造之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to make sth, especially by putting different parts together.
build

data.chText: 指制造、建造、修建（尤指房屋）：
data.enText: to make sth, especially a building, by putting parts together
a house built of stone

data.chText: 他们要在老发电站那里盖房子。
data.enText: They're going to build on the site of the old power station.
construct

data.chText: 指修建、建造（公路、房屋、机器等）
data.enText: [often passive] ( rather formal ) to build sth such as a road, building or machine
assemble

data.chText: 指装配、组装（家具、机器等）：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) to fit together all the separate parts of sth such as a piece of furniture or a machine
The cupboard is easy to assemble.
erect

data.chText: 指建立、建造、安装、竖立、搭起：
data.enText: ( formal ) to build sth; to put sth in position and make it stand upright

data.chText: 警察只得设立路障来阻截人群。
data.enText: Police had to erect barriers to keep crowds back.
set sth up
to build sth or place sth somewhere
We decided to set up camp for the night.
put sth up
to build sth or place sth somewhere

data.chText: 他们正在盖新旅馆以促进该地区的旅游业。
data.enText: They're putting up new hotels in order to boost tourism in the area.

data.chText: 用set sth up还是put sth up？
set sth up不用于永久性的建筑：
data.enText: Set sth up is not used for permanent buildings.
They're setting up new hotels.

data.chText: 搭帐篷用set up camp或put up a tent。搭建其他临时建筑用set up或put up均可：
data.enText: You set up camp but put up a tent . For other temporary structures you can use either word.
to set up/put up a fence/barrier/shelter
set sth up or put sth up?
put sth together
to make or prepare sth by fitting or collecting parts together
to put together a model plane
to build/construct/erect/put up a house/bridge/wall

simple_means.memory_skill: e 加强 + rect 正，直 → 竖直

ex.chText: 政府计划为当地居民建造新住宅。
ex.enText: The government plans to build new houses for local people.

ex.chText: 他白手起家建立了这家企业。
ex.enText: He built this business from scratch.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，应用范围最广，既可用于表示建造具体有形的建筑，又可用于表示抽象意义上的建立、构建。

ex.chText: 他们造这样一架飞机大约需要3年时间。
ex.enText: It takes them about three years to construct such an plane.

ex.chText: 这幢摩天大楼全部是用水泥和玻璃构筑的。
ex.enText: This skyscraper was constructed entirely of concrete and glass.

synonyms.bx: 强调按照一定设计建造规模较大、结构较复杂的物体，特别指按照图纸构筑某种建筑物。

ex.chText: 该城市将建造一座纪念碑。
ex.enText: A monument will be erected in this town.

synonyms.bx: 指建造高而垂直的建筑物，强调有一定高度。

ex.chText: 两国之间建立了良好的友谊。
ex.enText: A good friendship was established between the two countries.

ex.chText: 这家老字号公司创建于19世纪80年代。
ex.enText: This time-honored company was established in the 1880s.

synonyms.bx: 强调稳固地建成，可指建立国家、政府、学校或商店等，也可指建立信仰、名誉、法律、制度、关系等。

ex.chText: 这座城市由罗马人兴建。
ex.enText: This city was founded by the Romans.

ex.chText: 这些学者创办了一家教育机构。
ex.enText: The scholars have founded an educational institution.

synonyms.bx: 常指通过提供必要的资金创建城市、公司、学校等，含打下基础之意。

ex.chText: 那3个研究生曾想成立自己的出口公司。
ex.enText: Those three postgraduate students wanted to set up their own export business.

ex.chText: 你最好关注一下成立学术组织的新条例。
ex.enText: You'd better pay attention to the new regulations for setting up academic organizations.

synonyms.bx: 侧重指开始着手创建公司、机构、委员会等。

ex.chText: 那个图的纵轴代表什么？
ex.enText: What does the vertical axis of that graph represent?

ex.chText: 他们以前常去一个峭壁林立的峡谷。
ex.enText: They used to go to a gorge lined with vertical cliffs.

ex.chText: 滑雪中的“垂直落差”是什么意思？
ex.enText: What does 'vertical drop' mean in skiing?

synonyms.bx: 指与平面、水平线成 90 度角的，也可指沿此方向上升或下降的。

ex.chText: 一名服务生在他们餐桌旁笔直地站着。
ex.enText: A waiter stood erect beside their table.

synonyms.bx: 强调笔直挺拔的，而不是倾斜、弯曲或倒塌的。

ex.enText: He sat upright behind the desk.

ex.chText: 如果你非要带着这瓶颜料的话，你最让它保持直立。
ex.enText: If you have to carry this bottle of paint with you, then you'd better keep it upright.

synonyms.bx: 指站或坐得笔直的，也指处于竖直方向的。

example: for a dog, an erect tail indicates aggression
a column still vertical amid the ruins

value.def: If people erect something such as a building, bridge, or barrier, they build it or create it.

example.ex: Opposition demonstrators have erected barricades in roads leading to the parliament building...
example.tran: 反对派示威者已经在通往国会大厦的道路上设置了路障。

example.ex: We all unconsciously erect barriers against intimacy.
example.tran: 我们都会无意中对他人的亲近有所设防。

value.def: If you erect a system, a theory, or an institution, you create it.

example.ex: Japanese proprietors are erecting a complex infrastructure of political influence throughout America...
example.tran: 日本商人正在美国各地建立复杂的、具有政治影响力的基础结构。

example.ex: He erected a new doctrine of precedent.
example.tran: 他创立了一套新的判例原则。

example.ex: ...the whole edifice of free trade which has been erected since the Second World War.
example.tran: 第二次世界大战以来形成的整个自由贸易体系

value.tran: 建立（体制);创建（机构);创立（理论）

value.def: People or things that are erect are straight and upright.

example.ex: Stand reasonably erect, your arms hanging naturally...
example.tran: 挺身站直，双臂自然下垂。

example.ex: Her head was erect and her back was straight.
...the short, stiff, erect stems of almost bead-like blue flowers.
example.tran: 酷似小珠子的蓝色小花坚挺的短花茎

partsOfSpeech.dec: cor 加强 + rect 正，直 → 正确的
correct 正确的 + itude 表状态 → 行为端正
cor 加强 + rect 正，直 + ive …的 → 纠正的
di 二 + rect 正，直 → 直接连接两点的 → 直接的
direct 直接的 + ion 表名词 → 直着走下去 → 方向
e 加强 + rect 正，直 → 竖直
erect 直立的 + ion 表名词 → 直立，竖立
in 不 + correct 正确的 → 错误的
rect 正，直 + angle 角 →〔四个角〕都是直角 → 矩形
rect 正，直 + ify 使… → 使…正 → 改正〔错误〕
rect 正，直 + itude 表状态 → 正直；正确
